# .mailmap — canonical author/committer identity remapping.
#
# Remaps a compromised corporate address to the canonical personal
# identity for all of git's identity-aware tooling (git log --use-mailmap,
# git shortlog -sne, git blame, and GitHub's contributor/blame views).
#
# This is a DISPLAY remap, not a history rewrite: commit SHAs are unchanged and
# the raw address still exists in the object database. Chosen deliberately over
# a history rewrite because (a) the address is spread across 15 commits already
# published on origin/main, (b) rewriting would break the live epic-89 PR stack
# and every downstream clone, and (c) GitHub retains the old objects via merged
# PR records regardless, so a rewrite would pay maximum cost for an incomplete
# scrub. See epic-89 review thread for the full analysis.
#
# Format: Proper-Name <proper-email> <commit-email>
#         Proper-Name <proper-email> Commit-Name <commit-email>

mbtiongson1 <marco.tngsn@gmail.com> <marcus.rafael.tiongson@sap.com>
mbtiongson1 <marco.tngsn@gmail.com> Tiongson <marcus.rafael.tiongson@sap.com>
